{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EX3egyfhyPCE5vDZS7GWC9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is:\n1. DNS resolution for `elasticsearch-headless` is failing - \"failed to resolve host [elasticsearch-headless]\"\n2. The startup probe is failing\n\nThe DNS resolution failure is because `elasticsearch-headless` is a headless service, but it seems ES is using a domain search path that doesn't include the right domain. Let me check if the service has a proper selector and if it's in the same namespace.\n\nWait, the error says `java.net.UnknownHostException: elasticsearch-headless`. This means the DNS lookup for `elasticsearch-headless` is failing. Let me check:\nI'm realizing there's a chicken-and-egg problem here - the headless service needs pod endpoints to function, but Elasticsearch needs the headless service to discover other nodes during startup. The service selector should be matching the pods, but since no pods are ready yet, there are no endpoints available for DNS to resolve.\n\nThe solution is to set `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service, which allows it to include all running pods in DNS resolution regardless of their ready status. This is a standard requirement for StatefulSet-based Elasticsearch deployments.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1593,"cache_read_input_tokens":51212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1593},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2470940c-181d-4c7f-b8de-3d45f7e78183","uuid":"f5d572ec-1bec-4519-b33e-f663a02b4559","request_id":"req_011CcP9RePBqXCSYpLXVm9Mm"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EX3egyfhyPCE5vDZS7GWC9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The headless service resolves only to Ready pod IPs, causing a chicken-and-egg problem: ES can't discover peers until all pods are Ready, but pods can't become Ready until the cluster forms. I need `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1593,"cache_read_input_tokens":51212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1593},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2470940c-181d-4c7f-b8de-3d45f7e78183","uuid":"8346f12c-db64-453a-9d44-6b100d48b4d6","request_id":"req_011CcP9RePBqXCSYpLXVm9Mm"}
