{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NABUBfw1JswHoz9Av2fsLm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The main issue is the DNS resolution of `elasticsearch-headless`. This is failing because:\n1. The headless service DNS only resolves to pods that are Ready\n2. No pods are Ready (chicken-and-egg)\n\nBut wait, why can't ES resolve `elasticsearch-headless` at all? In Kubernetes, a headless service DNS entry IS created even when no pods are backing it - it just returns an empty DNS response (NXDOMAIN or empty answer). But actually, with a headless service, if there are no ready endpoints, the DNS might return NXDOMAIN or the A record might not exist.\nActually, I realize the issue: without `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`, the headless service won't return DNS records for pods that aren't ready yet, which creates the bootstrap problem. I need to enable that flag so the service returns all pod IPs regardless of readiness state.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":865,"cache_read_input_tokens":53695,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":865},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2470940c-181d-4c7f-b8de-3d45f7e78183","uuid":"156102c7-745b-44d8-80cf-eb47a3cb59e3","request_id":"req_011CcP9TKLGSJJpCErp7CCWP"}
